  "contents": "<article>\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb-container\">\n    <div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n      <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n        {\n          \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\",\n          \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\",\n          \"itemListElement\": [\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api\", \"name\": \"API\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core\", \"name\": \"@angular/core\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core/InputSignal\", \"name\": \"InputSignal\" } }\n          ]\n        }\n      </script>\n        <a href=\"/api\">API</a> > <a href=\"api/core\">@angular/core</a>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"github-links\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/src/authoring/input/input_signal.ts#L85-L97\" aria-label=\"View Source\" title=\"View Source\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">code</i></a>\n</div>\n  </div>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"inputsignal\">InputSignal<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/InputSignal#inputsignal\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label interface\">interface</label>\n    <label class=\"api-status-label dev-preview\" title=\"This API is in Developer Preview\">\n      <a href=\"guide/releases#developer-preview\">developer preview</a>\n    </label>\n    \n  </header>\n  <aio-toc class=\"embedded\"></aio-toc>\n\n  <div class=\"api-body\">\n  <section class=\"short-description\">\n    <p><code><a href=\"api/core/InputSignal\" class=\"code-anchor\">InputSignal</a></code> represents a special <code><a href=\"api/core/Signal\" class=\"code-anchor\">Signal</a></code> for a directive/component input.</p>\n\n    <p><a href=\"api/core/InputSignal#description\">See more...</a></p>\n  </section><section class=\"interface-overview\">\n<code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\">\ninterface <a href=\"api/core/InputSignal\" class=\"code-anchor\">InputSignal</a>&#x3C;T> extends <a href=\"api/core/InputSignalWithTransform\" class=\"code-anchor\">InputSignalWithTransform</a>&#x3C;T, T> {\n\n  // inherited from <a class=\"code-anchor\" href=\"api/core/InputSignalWithTransform\">core/InputSignalWithTransform</a>\n}\n</code-example>\n\n\n</section>\n\n<section class=\"see-also\">\n  <h2 id=\"see-also\">See also<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/InputSignal#see-also\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <ul>\n    <li><a href=\"api/core/InputOptionsWithTransform\"><code>InputOptionsWithTransform</code></a>\n<p> for inputs with transforms.</p></li>\n  </ul>\n</section>\n  \n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\">Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/InputSignal#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>An input signal is similar to a non-writable signal except that it also\ncarries additional type-information for transforms, and that Angular internally\nupdates the signal whenever a new value is bound.</p>\n</section>\n  \n  \n</div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/core\n - api/core/InputFunction\n - api/core/InputSignalWithTransform\n - guide/model-inputs\n - guide/signal-inputs\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/core\n - api/core/InputOptionsWithTransform\n - api/core/InputSignal#description\n - api/core/InputSignal#inputsignal\n - api/core/InputSignal#see-also\n - api/core/InputSignalWithTransform\n - api/core/Signal\n - guide/releases#developer-preview\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/src/authoring/input/input_signal.ts#L85-L97\n-->"
